# === agentic-harness baseline gitignore additions ===
# Appended to project .gitignore by harness-init.
# Project-specific additions go AFTER this block.
#
# Note on .planning/ and .beads/:
#   This baseline un-ignores both for the harness repo's own use (the harness
#   IS what it's building, so its scaffolding is a tracked build artifact).
#   In adopter repos, harness-init appends an "adopter overlay" AFTER this
#   block that re-ignores both directories — they hold operator-local state
#   (sprint plans, token ledger, AI-critic outputs) and must not be shared
#   between collaborators of the adopter project. See docs/ADOPTION.md.

# === Hidden directories ===
# Ignore any hidden directory by default; explicitly allow the ones tracked.
.*/
!.beads/
!.planning/
!.github/

# === macOS ===
.DS_Store

# === Common IDE / editor state ===
.vscode/
.idea/
.fleet/
.zed/
.cursor/
.vs/

# === Token-accounting ephemeral state ===
# token-ledger.jsonl is committed (auditable per-bead history).
# active-bead is the orchestrator's current claim; ephemeral, machine-local.
.beads/active-bead

# === External AI critic outputs ===
# Process reviews from external AI critics (Codex/GPT-5/etc.) stay local.
# Canonical findings flow into beads + briefs, not into the repo.
.planning/audit-reviews/

# === Project-generated calibration data (uncomment per project) ===
# Synthetic / LLM-generated calibration data is regenerable, not canonical.
# .planning/<scope>/test-corpus/synthetic/
# .planning/<scope>/test-corpus/gold/raw/   # raw interview audio/transcripts per CONSENT

# === agentic-harness adopter overlay ===
# Harness scaffolding (.planning/, .beads/) is operator-local state.
# Ignored in adopter repos; tracked only in the harness repo itself.
.planning/
.beads/
# Codex per-operator state (rules, sessions, local plugin cache).
.codex/
